U.S. Government source (USGS): Describes the United States as 'The 50 States and the District of Columbia.' — https://www.usgs.gov/faqs/what-constitutes-united-states-what-are-official-definitions
Conclusion: Multiple authoritative sources state the United States has 50 states (plus D.C. and territories). The claim 'There are 51 states in America.' is incorrect.
